<TITLE> BNP nominates wives of convicted leaders </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 29 (bdnews24.com)  Among the list of BNP hopefuls announced Saturday are a raft of wives of convicted party leaders, masquerading as 'new faces' and 'the female quota'. Those named for party tickets to constituencies of their convict husbands include: Afroza Abbas alongside her ex-minister husband Mirza Abbas (Dhaka-8), Sabina Yesmin, wife of former state minister Ruhul Kuddus Talukdar Dulu (Natore-2), Majeda Ahsan Munshi, wife of former MP Manjurul Ahsan Munshi (Comilla-4), Sabera Aman, wife of ex-MP Amanullah Aman (Dhaka-2), Nasima Akhtar wife of ex-MP Nasiruddin Pintu (Dhaka-7) and Hasina Ahmed, wife of ex-MP Salauddin Ahmed (Cox's Bazar-1). In the same vein is the nomination of Afroza Khan Mita, daughter of convicted ex-MP Harun Or Rashid Khan Monno (Manikganj-2). Selima Rahman (Barisal-3), Shahida Akter (Jamalpur-1), Ismat Sultana Ilen Bhutto (Jalkathi-2) and Helen Zereen Khan (Madaripur-2) are among the party's other women nominees. bdnews
